HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 171
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Michael Bittel of
Knoxville to the heritage conservation trust fund
board of trustees.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 11-7-104(a), provides for the creation
of the heritage conservation trust fund board of trustees; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 11-7-104(b), provides that the
governor shall appoint eleven (11) members to the board; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Michael Bittel of Knoxville as a member of
the heritage conservation trust fund board representing East Tennessee, to a term that will
expire on October 31, 2027; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Bittel previously served as the CEO of the Adirondack Chamber of
Commerce in New York, and before that, he was the co-CEO of The King Arthur Flour Co. in
Vermont and the COO of Hometown Healthcare; and
WHEREAS, he already serves as one of the public members on the Tennessee board of
medical examiners; and
WHEREAS, Michael Bittel has vast experience in the agricultural field, ranging from
advising members of the U.S. Congress on agricultural policy to chairing multiple committees
dealing with land conservation; he wrote two land conservation bills that were ultimately added
to the 2014 Farm Bill and passed by Congress; and
WHEREAS, he is also an avid hunter/fisherman/outdoorsman who has a passion for
land conservation; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Bittel graduated from Skidmore College in 1989 with a degree in
business and government; and
